{[showcards S:H4]

You are South. The bidding has been as shown.

You lead the \CK and continue with the \CJ then \CQ, taken by East's \CA. To trick 4 East plays the \H4. What do you play?

Play the \HQ.

To see why you should play the \HQ, just visualize the result if you play low. East will finesse with dummy's \H8. If North wins his \HJ on this trick there will be 4 good \H tricks in dummy. If North withholds his \HJ then Declarer will have 3 \H winners.

Now visualize the result of playing the \HQ. Whether East takes this trick or not he cannot win more than 2 \Hs.}
[Play "W"]CK

